    "reasoning": "To implement the thermostat controller, I need to analyze the logic based on the mode (heating or cooling) and the temperature conditions (too_cold, too_hot) along with the user's fan request (fan_on). In heating mode (mode=1), the heater should turn on when too_cold=1 and the fan should also turn on when either the heater is on or fan_on=1. In cooling mode (mode=0), the air conditioner should turn on when too_hot=1 and the fan should also turn on when either the aircon is on or fan_on=1. Since this is purely combinational logic, I'll use always @(*) for the combinational blocks. All signals are declared as logic as required. I will avoid using 'inside', 'unique', or 'unique0' keywords as per the guidelines.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input mode,\n    input too_cold,\n    input too_hot,\n    input fan_on,\n    output heater,\n    output aircon,\n    output fan\n);\n\n    // Combinational logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (mode) begin\n            // Heating mode\n            heater = too_cold;\n            aircon = 1'b0;\n            fan = heater | fan_on;\n        end else begin\n            // Cooling mode\n            heater = 1'b0;\n            aircon = too_hot;\n            fan = aircon | fan_on;\n        end\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
